title: For Sale/Trade:  Customized Blued Rock Island 1911 45cal
postcontent:
This 1911 was a standard GI 1911.  It was stripped to bare metal, hand polished, and blued (I should mention that it was hot blued in a blueing tank, it WAS NOT blued using the rub on stuff).  Parts such as the barrel bushing, trigger, hammer, etc. were polished and left in the white.  It now has pearl grips on it that were hand polished.

For those who don't know what blueing is, it's a a process that turns the metal blue (black), but will allow it to shine.  The standard GI, and most other guns, are parkerized.  Parkerizing is a similar process but coasts the metal in a matte black finish.

I still have the wood handgrips that I'll give with the pistol.  I also have 2 magazine that will go with it.

I'm selling so I can buy a Sig Sauer SP2022 in 40cal but will also trade for one or a similar pistol, possibly a Glock.  I'm looking for a duty gun in 40cal.
